---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

```
Frontend     →  Streamlit
AI (Primary) →  Gemini 1.5 Flash API (free tier)
AI (Fallback)→  Ollama gemma3:1b (local)
Compute      →  Python / Pandas
Charts       →  Plotly
PDF Report   →  fpdf2 + kaleido
Excel Report →  openpyxl
Memory       →  JSON (RAG-style)
```

---

## ⚡ Quick Start (Local)

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/AbuAsifAnsari/smart-data-analyst.git
cd smart-data-analyst
```

### 2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Add your Gemini API key
Create a `.env` file in project root:
```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
```
Get your free key at → [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com)

### 4. Run the app
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
smart_data_analyst/
├── app.py                    # Main Streamlit app
├── requirements.txt
├── .env                      # API key (not in repo)
│
├── utils/
│   ├── data_loader.py        # CSV/Excel file handler
│   ├── ollama_chat.py        # AI engine (Gemini + Ollama)
│   ├── dashboard.py          # KPI detection + compute
│   ├── chart_agent.py        # Auto chart generator
│   ├── memory_engine.py      # RAG memory (JSON)
│   ├── history_manager.py    # Chat history persistence
│   └── report_generator.py   # PDF + Excel reports
│
├── memory/                   # Auto-created at runtime
│   ├── qa_log.json
│   └── chat_history.json
│
└── uploads/                  # Auto-created at runtime
```

---

## 🤖 How the AI Works

```
User Question
      ↓
Intent Detection (wise/by/top N/average...)
      ↓
Python Compute (Pandas — fast & accurate)
      ↓ if complex question
Gemini API (primary — better reasoning)
      ↓ if API limit
Ollama gemma3:1b (local fallback)
      ↓
Answer + Table + Chart + Python Code
```

---

## 📊 Supported Question Types

```
✅ What is the total revenue?
✅ Top 5 products by revenue
✅ Region wise revenue vs quantity
✅ What is the average order value?
✅ How many missing values are there?
✅ Correlation between revenue and quantity?
✅ Show me a chart of sales by category
```

---

## 🌐 Deploy on Streamlit Cloud

1. Push code to GitHub
2. Go to [share.streamlit.io](https://share.streamlit.io)
3. Connect your repo → select `app.py`
4. Add secret: `GEMINI_API_KEY = "your_key"`
5. Deploy ✅

